title: The Penn State report card: Maryland edition
text:
The Penn State report card: Maryland edition Penn State vs Maryland Patrick Semansky / AP Penn State coach James Franklin greets wide receiver Chris Godwin (12) and quarterback Christian Hackenberg as they jog off the field after a touchdown in the first half against Maryland on Saturday. Penn State coach James Franklin greets wide receiver Chris Godwin (12) and quarterback Christian Hackenberg as they jog off the field after a touchdown in the first half against Maryland on Saturday. (Patrick Semansky / AP) The Penn State report card after a 31-30 win over Maryland 
OFFENSE: B-. Sloppy though they were, Lions deserve credit for taking (and hitting) so many plays downfield. Receiver Chris Godwin is a budding star. 
DEFENSE: B-. Sloppy though they were, Lions shut down Terps four times in 4 t h quarter with the game on the line. 
SPECIAL TEAMS: C. Punter Daniel Pasquariello was much better, and Nick Scott had several good kickoff returns (though he did fumble). 
COACHING: B-. Offense reacted well to the run-stopping defensive fronts Maryland brought. Defense struggled with a running QB but forced five turnovers. 
OVERALL: B-. A big, fat sloppy win.
